casebody.data:
John R. GERARDY, Relator,
v.
ANAGRAM INTERNATIONAL and Liberty Mutual Insurance Company, Respondents,
and
John Stark, M.D. and Brooklyn Center Chiropractic, Intervenors. A17-1507 Supreme Court of Minnesota. Dated: April 25, 2018 John R. Gerardy, Bloomington, Minnesota, pro se. Janet Monson, Jacob R. Colling, Aafedt, Forde, Gray, Monson, and Hager P.A., for respondents.

ORDER

Based upon all the files, records, and proceedings herein,

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED that the decision of the Workers' Compensation Court of Appeals filed September 15, 2017, be, and the same is, affirmed without opinion. See Hoff v. Kempton, 317 N.W.2d 361 , 366 (Minn. 1982) (summary dispositions have no precedential value because they do not commit the court to any particular point of view doing no more than establishing the law of the case).
